{"_type": "issue", "id": "demo-xy3", "title": "Calendar view flickers on Safari", "description": "## Repro\n\nThe calendar card **flickers** on first paint in Safari 17.\n\n1. Open `/calendar` in Safari\n2. Observe the event preview flash\n\nRoot cause is a `useLayoutEffect` racing the calendar fetch \u2014 see [the thread](https://example.test).\n\n- [ ] confirm on iOS Safari\n- [ ] check the reduced-motion path", "notes": "2026-07-06: reproduced on Safari 17.4; not on Chrome. Likely the event preview.", "status": "open", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "owner": "alex@example.com", "created_at": "2026-07-08T17:16:07Z", "created_by": "Alex Rivera", "updated_at": "2026-07-08T09:00:00Z", "dependencies": [{"issue_id": "demo-xy3", "depends_on_id": "demo-kzr.2", "type": "blocks", "created_at": "2026-07-08T10:16:08Z", "created_by": "Alex Rivera", "metadata": "{}"}], "comments": [{"id": "019f42be-201c-792f-b57c-a67fa37c86b0", "issue_id": "demo-xy3", "author": "Alex Rivera", "text": "Confirmed on iOS Safari 17.4 too \u2014 the event preview races the layout effect. Proposing a useEffect guard.", "created_at": "2026-07-08T17:19:44Z"}, {"id": "019f42be-214d-78a2-bc46-422c8146c4ce", "issue_id": "demo-xy3", "author": "Alex Rivera", "text": "Assigning to the calendar team; ties into the calendar view work.", "created_at": "2026-07-08T17:19:44Z"}], "dependency_count": 1, "dependent_count": 0, "comment_count": 2}
