{"_type": "issue", "id": "demo-hw", "title": "Reflow torture: hard-wrapped paragraph vs intended list", "status": "open", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "owner": "alex@example.com", "created_at": "2026-07-08T17:16:20Z", "created_by": "Alex Rivera", "updated_at": "2026-07-08T09:00:00Z", "dependency_count": 0, "dependent_count": 0, "comment_count": 0, "description": "The importer processes each row in a strict priority order, and this\n- line begins with a dash, so a CommonMark parser reads it as a bullet list\nitem even though it is really a hard-wrapped continuation of the sentence,\n1. and this line starts with one-dot which interrupts the paragraph as an\nordered list, fragmenting one thought into three mis-parsed blocks below.\n\nA genuinely intended list, one item per stored line, wraps cleanly:\n\n- validate the header before processing any rows\n- normalize each value against the declared column type\n- write valid rows and report rejected ones separately"}
